Teachers are not able to keep a distance from their students, its ~30 people in one room working in very close proximity, touching and retouching the same surfaces and kids constantly coming right up to to their teacher's face to ask questions, talk, tattle etc. It talks about the danger of an incubation period of ONE person in a car with ONE other person... and then schools of 600 kids and adults in close contact, constantly sharing air are supposed to keep on keepin on?!?! It's great that kids aren't getting sick but what about all the adults in the building and their adult family members and what about the children's parents and grandparents who they go home to?

snippet.textDisplay: 6 months?  Why has it only lasted 3 months in Asia?  What most people seem to be failing to realize is that these viruses are finite...they do not keep on killing and infecting indefinitely.  Eventually the virus simply ceases to exist...it runs its course and dies.  My big concern with Covid-19 in North America is when we get a spike of cases that suddenly flood our hospitals, we then overwhelm our medical capacity to help people, and ambulances will be turned away at hospitals with totally non-Covid-19 related conditions (e.g. heart attacks, strokes etc.).
